  <rte>
    <name>Netherbeck Horseshoe - Middle Fell, Steeple and Red Pike</name>
    <desc>This is a demanding Lake District walk including seven 'tops' in the Western Fells of Lakeland. Generally the route follows clear paths certainly once Steeple has been reached. However the first half of the walk sees relatively few walkers and some navigational skills may be required in periods of poor visibility. </desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1690-description</url>
